---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith("/")
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
---

<BaseLayout title="Yoga Lightness Beta" description="A clean theme shell for Jane's new Yoga Lightness copy.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">New Copy Coming</p>
      <h1>Yoga Lightness</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A calm public shell for Jane's new writing, classes, and reflective yoga
        work. Old website content has been removed from this beta.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button" href={`${base}theme-preview/`}>View themes</a>
        <a class="button secondary" href={`${base}blog/`}>Copy notes</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-panel" aria-hidden="true">
      <span></span>
      <span></span>
      <span></span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>What This Is</h2>
    <p>
      This is no longer a migration preview. It is a clean staging site for new
      Yoga Lightness copy. The immediate job is to find a visual direction that
      suits Jane's new text, then build around that rather than around the old
      site.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="feature-grid" aria-label="Draft site shape">
    <article>
      <h2>Home</h2>
      <p>A short, warm entry point that says who Jane helps and what the work feels like.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>Classes</h2>
      <p>A practical page for current classes, workshops, contact, and booking next steps.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h2>About</h2>
      <p>A personal page shaped around Jane's new copy rather than inherited wording.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section split">
    <div>
      <h2>Review Notes</h2>
      <p>
        The safest beta is now copy-first. Once Jane sends the new text, the site
        can grow from actual language instead of placeholder assumptions.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="note-panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Current State</p>
      <p>Old scrape removed. Waiting for Jane's new copy and theme direction.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
